added.title: Subway
added.description: The Bears are stranded on a subway platform after missing their train. But while waiting, the Bears are challenged with recovering some lost items.

added.title: Anger Management
added.description: In order to appear on a successful kids show, Nom Nom must successfully complete anger management, with Grizz as his partner.

added.title: Panda's Friend
added.description: Panda uses an app to find a friend with whom he has more common with. Soon things take a turn for the worse when the new friend gets too possessive.

added.title: Neighbors
added.description: Some new neighbors set up camp next to the Bears' cave. Panda and Ice love it, but Grizz thinks they're up to no good.

added.title: Professor Lampwick
added.description: Chloe's professor is too mean to give her any face time to talk over her poor grade. The Bears take things into their own hands to help, causing big trouble for Chloe.

added.title: Ralph
added.description: Charlie meets a creature just like him named Ralph. Charlie loves having a new friend, but the Bears think Ralph is bad news.

added.title: Planet Bears
added.description: A nature documentary follows the Bears through their normal routine, which includes a trip to the grocery store.

added.title: Coffee Cave
added.description: After finding out Ice Bear is a master barista, the Bears turn their cave into a popular coffee shop. But it all goes awry when Ice Bear gets too into coffee and goes berserk.

added.title: Charlie's Big Foot
added.description: After Charlie hurts his foot, The Bears have to sneak him into a hospital for medical assistance.

added.title: The Demon
added.description: Chloe and Ice Bear accidentally lose Chloe's prized hoodie to the ferocious dog next store. They go on a mission to get it back.

added.title: Panda's Art
added.description: Panda paints a portrait of Charlie and it's a hit with his art class. But after an art dealer offers to buy the painting, Panda has to get it back from Charlie.

added.title: Poppy Rangers
added.description: Ranger Tabes leads a troop of young girls into a cave expedition, and brings Grizz as their cave expert.

added.title: Lucy's Brother
added.description: To impress Lucy Panda offers to babysit her brother, Clifford. But Clifford turns out to be too high maintenance for Panda to handle.

added.title: Private Lake
added.description: When the local lake is overcrowded with tourists, the Bears have fun at Charlie's private lake.

added.title: Lunch with Tabes
added.description: When Tabes's lunch gets stolen, Tabes launches a full investigation to find the culprit.

added.title: Road Trip
added.description: Chloe and the Bears take a road trip to see a meteor shower. Ice Bear, the only one licensed to drive, is put in charge, which becomes harder than he thought.

added.title: Summer Love
added.description: Panda goes on a mission to return a lost phone to the girl of his dreams.

added.title: The Kitty
added.description: After a mishap in the forest, the Bears lose their own home to dangerous animals.

added.title: Crowbar Jones
added.description: Grizz screens an epic amateur movie he just made for a focus group. But when he notices people are leaving he must figure out ways to keep the audience engaged.

added.title: Dog Hotel
added.description: With no place to stay while their cave gets fumigated, the Bears book a night at a hotel for dogs.

added.title: Bear Lift
added.description: To help raise money to save Darrell's store, the Bears use the stack as a taxi through a ride share app.

added.title: The Nom Nom Show
added.description: Things go awry while Nom Nom shoots his first television show. The Bears offer to help and appear on the show.

added.title: Ice Cave
added.description: Ralph takes over the cave and turns it into a snowy fortress where he reigns as king over the Bears and Charlie.

added.title: Spa Day
added.description: The Bears have a relaxing day at the spa. Grizz tries to get everything the spa has to offer. Panda gets trapped in the steam room with an old man. And Ice Bear plays ping pong.

added.title: Charlie's Halloween Thing
added.description: Charlie hosts an evening of spooky stories starring the Bears.

added.title: Bunnies
added.description: The Baby Bears meet a group of helpless bunnies. When they find out the bunnies live in fear of vicious crows, the Bears decide to become heroes and help out.

added.title: Pigeons
added.description: Grizz becomes best buds with a flock of pigeons.

added.title: Panda 2
added.description: Baby Panda happily lives in a closed off environment for study. But when he's given a new friend, Panda 2, his worldview is shaken, which sets him off on a great adventure.

added.title: Tubin'
added.description: In search of some adventure, the Bears ride a tube down a dangerous river.

added.title: Ranger Games
added.description: Grizz helps Ranger Tabes and the Poppy Rangers play a game of kickball against their rivals.

added.title: The Perfect Tree
added.description: Chloe and Ice Bear drive up north to find the perfect Christmas tree. Meanwhile, Grizz and Panda are in charge of decorating Chloe's house.

added.title: Bearz II Men
added.description: The Baby Bears help a teenager accomplish his dream of being a famous singer.

added.title: Bro Brawl
added.description: The Bears participate in a brother-themed game show against Panda's ex-BFF, Tom, and his roommates.

added.title: The Park
added.description: The Bears spend a day at the park. Grizz works out. Panda attempts to sell his artwork. Ice Bear trains some kids.

added.title: I Am Ice Bear
added.description: After Ice Bear hits his head, Grizz and Panda notice him acting like a different person.

added.title: Baby Bears Can't Jump
added.description: In order to win a pizza, the Baby Bears play basketball against a ragtag gang of kids.

added.title: Go Fish
added.description: While on a fishing trip, the Bears get attacked by a giant legendary fish.

added.title: Teacher's Pet
added.description: The Baby Bears escape their hectic lives by attending school.

added.title: Googs
added.description: The Bears win a tour of the infamous Googs corporate headquarters.

added.title: Paperboyz
added.description: The Baby Bears get jobs as paper boys.

added.title: Bear Squad
added.description: Tabes deputizes the Bears so they can go to the city and catch a thief.

added.title: I, Butler
added.description: The Bears use a robot bear to help around the house. But things get tricky when they lose control of the robot.

added.title: Best Bears
added.description: The Bears must complete their Best-Man duties on the day of Darrell's wedding.

added.title: Chata's Quinta Quinceañera
added.description: Vic and Val want to go to a friend's pool party on the same day as their grandma's quinceañera, so they use a magical flute that allows them to teleport and attend both at the same time.

added.title: Quintos Quinces
added.description: Victor y Valentino quieren ir a la fiesta en la piscina de un amigo el mismo día que la fiesta de quince años de su abuela, así que usan una flauta mágica que les permite teletransportarse y asistir a ambas al mismo tiempo.

added.title: Amor de hermanos
added.description: Después de romper la planta de Chata, Vic y Val deben cumplir con la tarea aparentemente fácil de reemplazarla, lo cual demuestra no serlo cuando sus disputas ponen en peligro Monte Macabro.
